news.title: Home registrations in Kolkata drop by 13% in July 2024
news.para: Home sale registrations in Kolkata saw an 18% decline in July, influenced by the state government's removal of incentives such as a stamp duty cut and reduction in circle rates. The Bengal chapter of Credai has requested a reconsideration, arguing that lower stamp duties would boost sales and contribute to the state exchequer.

news.title: Goa urban development minister directs civic bodies to take services online
news.para: Vishwajit Rane, the urban development minister, directed all municipalities to provide their civic services online within 15 days. He instructed chief officers to inspect their jurisdictions and identify unused funds for utilization. Rane also discussed regularizing contractual municipal employees and announced nearly complete GIS mapping for North Goa towns, with similar plans for South Goa.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group forecasts bigger net loss in H1 2024
news.para: China's property sector, a key driver of the economy, has been in turmoil since 2021, with housing sales plummeting 6.5% in 2023 from the previous year and 35.9% from its 2021 peak, following a regulatory crackdown on high leverage among developers that sparked a liquidity crisis.

news.title: South Korea holds interest rate amid property concerns
news.para: The Bank of Korea held its benchmark interest rate at 3.50% at its monetary policy review, as expected by 38 out of 40 economists surveyed by Reuters.

news.title: Developers struggle to find quality contractors amid housing boom
news.para: Many developers are boosting in-house capabilities while some are getting global contractors to ensure there is no delay in project delivery, industry insiders told ET. Some are also engaging construction tech companies.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP officials convert public path into private property with fake khata certificates
news.para: BBMP revenue department officials have demonstrated that even a public road, existing for over 40 years, is not safe from being falsely converted into private property by corrupt revenue officers in Bommanahalli Zone.

news.title: Manoj Bajpayee sells apartment in Mumbai’s Mahalaxmi for Rs 9 crore
news.para: The apartment on the 47th floor of one of the wings of the upcoming tower on Boricha Marg is spread over 1,247 sq ft. The owner of the apartment will also get exclusive access to two car parking slots.

news.title: Hiranandani's Greenbase to develop industrial, logistics parks on 391 acres in Chennai
news.para: This land acquisition is expected to take the company’s total land holding to 391 acres in Chennai and Greenbase is planning to invest over Rs 700 crore to develop these land parcels into industrial parks in the current financial year itself.

news.title: General Atlantic, Pioneer Fund sell 5.37% stake in PNB Housing for Rs 1,119 crore
news.para: According to the block deal data available on the BSE, General Atlantic, through its arm General Atlantic Singapore Fund FII, sold 1,33,25,074 shares or 5.13 per cent stake in PNB Housing Finance.

news.title: Haryana RERA slaps penalty on promoter of 1000 Trees Housing
news.para: The penalty was imposed after scrutiny of the application of the promoter seeking registration of the project to complete construction and hand over units to homebuyers.

news.title: In Belagavi, land issues hinder development, delay central schemes
news.para: The central govt projects - Belagavi Ring Road, Halaga-Macche bypass highway, and the Belagavi-Dharwad new railway line project - are facing setbacks due to delays in land acquisition.

news.title: Investment of sale proceeds from depreciated asset into home qualify for tax benefits: ITAT
news.para: The ITAT Mumbai ruled that tax benefits could be claimed for investing in a residential property even if the investment came from selling a depreciated asset, like an office unit. Ms SP Khanna utilized this provision, selling her office and investing in a new residential property, ultimately benefiting under Section 54-F of the Income-tax Act.

news.title: Embassy REIT lease out 1.4 million sq ft office space in Bengaluru to Commonwealth Bank of Australia
news.para: Embassy REIT owns and operates a 51 million sq ft portfolio of 14 office parks in Bengaluru, Mumbai, Pune, the National Capital Region and Chennai. Its portfolio comprises 37.7 million sq ft of completed operating area.

news.title: Keystone Realtors to invest Rs 900 crore in residential projects in FY25: Boman Irani, CMD
news.para: Earlier this month, Keystone Realtors reported a 45 per cent decline in its consolidated net profit at Rs 25.82 crore for the June quarter of this fiscal on higher expenses.

news.title: Around two lakh property owners in Pune fail to claim 40% tax discount
news.para: Only owners of 2.5 lakh of 4.5 lakh properties, liable for submission of the forms, have done so, the official said. The deadline for submission of the forms ended on August 15.

news.title: Wells Fargo to sell its non-agency third-party commercial mortgage servicing business to Trimont
news.para: Founded in 1988, Trimont, which primarily serves non-bank and alternative lenders, will manage combined $640 billion loans in the U.S. after deal is closed.

news.title: Square One builds up presence in Hyderabad to target exponential growth in the city for FY 2024-25
news.para: “Hyderabad offers us the perfect canvas to put forth our creative services. There is a constant demand to outdo whatever has ever come before, and that's a challenge that we like to take up with every real estate project.” - Nishant Mehta, Director, Square One.

news.title: Five years after Gurugram civic body took over, infra crumbles in South City 1
news.para: Roads, many of which are in a state of disrepair, are riddled with potholes. The lack of adequate street lights, residents said, exacerbates the situation, causing difficulties for them while commuting and posing a risk of accidents, particularly at night.

news.title: General Atlantic set to sell up to 5.1% stake in PNB Housing via open market on Aug 21
news.para: According to a term sheet issued by IIFL Securities, General Atlantic Singapore Fund FII Pte will sell 1.33 crore shares at a floor price of Rs 775 apiece, aiming to raise Rs 1,033 crore.

news.title: Assam town & country planning advisory council meeting approves master plans for 11 towns
news.para: The committee convened a significant meeting today at Janata Bhawan, with the presence of Housing and Urban Affairs and Irrigation Minister Ashok Singhal, Revenue and Disaster Management Minister Jogen Mohan and several MLAs.
